    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in China (
                        Stuart
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d49</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">49</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-04-03T02:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-04-03T02:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-03T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-03T02:00:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-03T15:00:00+08:00">April 3, 1948—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 3—4:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>602. Embassy has had nothing to do with subject Deptel 479, April 2, 5 p.m.
                    ComNavWesPac’s Top Secret 2908552Z, 29 March 1948 commenting on CinCFE’s 261001Z
                    regarding direct supply of munitions to Nationalist Forces was seen by us. It
                    was message commenting on one from Department of Army to General Barr which was
                    repeated to CinCFE which in turn repeated it to ComNavWesPac. Army message to
                    Barr which was shown to us appeared to us one involving precautionary planning
                    in case Army was asked by Congressional Committee whether additional military
                    aid might be possible. We did not seek, nor have we received advice from <pb facs="0062" n="52" xml:id="pg_52"/> ComNavWesPac on subject. We have taken
                    no action in respect thereof.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
